description: Licensed since 1992"I am proud of the reputation for honesty and excellent client service for which the Guarantee Corporations are known. title: Realtor
description: I grew up knowing the term, "landlord" before I ever heard the term "Realtor".Let alone, I met my first Real Estate Agent in person not too long ago in my life.I was born in Fresno California. I lived in various sides of town. Majority spent in the south parts of Fresno. As far back as I could remember, I started out in Eastside Fresno. Near Cedar & Tulare.Then, moved to South Sacramento near 47th and MLK. Where I began my schooling at Pacific Elementary. Right after Kindergardten we moved back to Fresno to the Westside of Fresno. Where I continued my growth in a neighborhood called, Sunset and attended Edison-Bethune. Wawona middle school and Edison High.I was fortunate enough to live the next 10 years here on Valencia Avenue before my family and I started moving around living in a handful of areas in a short period of time. Where we finally settled in the Highway City area where I finished my Junior year at Central East.Senior year, I had to go into independent studies for a couple months. While we moved back to South Sacramento off of Fruitridge & 44th. This is where I attended & graduated from Hiram Johnson.Oh did I mention I am the oldest out of 9 siblings. I lived out majority of my life with my 4 brothers & sister though. As of today, I had to go my own path that led me here at this point of my journey.When I came back to Fresno right after highschool. I came back alone. I knew the only advice I could follow, was to go back to school. Which I entered in Fresno City to begin my pursuit in Business.After a few semesters, I dropped out. I left because life started getting more serious than I could handle but I handled it the best I can.I worked a warehouse job while trying to figure out how I could create my own job. How can I create my own business? That was my question, which kept me looking in the Entrepreneurial route.By no means is it an easy route. It requires alot of personal growth and dedication. I tried to start a t-shirt printing business with my family when they came back to Fresno. This is where I started to build on my Graphic Design knowledge which was just a highschool class worth of experience. I also picked up a camera to begin shooting photography as a professional amateur.Life took its course with the t-shirt business and I chose to leave it and go my own path. I picked up a job through Fresno Unified School District as a member in the Food Service industry. It was one of the best decisions I ever made as a young man. I really appreciated that job. It kept me afloat where I was still fortunate enough to keep pursuing my goals. It taught me how to run a small business in sense through managing a cafeteria on my own as a one person show.Oh I also didn't mention that dogs; particularly American Pitbulls & American Bullies have a significant influence on my life from a very early age. But most importantly in my early 20s, I was traveling and showing my American Bullies. This is a whole story within itself.But let's just stay within this lane. During my time with Fresno Unified, I continued to build on my knowledge about Graphic Design, Photography, & Bully Shows.But at some point through all this, Real Estate chose me. And I finally realized what my pursuit in Entrepreneurship has led me to become in life. I spent 2 years studying and preparing for my exam. I re-enrolled into Fresno City. And the Real Estate textbooks thoroughly, cover to cover. I wanted to know I was well prepared. I needed to feel prepared. I only wanted to take it once. Because I only had one shot to make it all happen, my back was against the wall.March 2021 during the peak of the pandemic. I traveled to Sacramento with my lovely spouse who been apart of my journey since my early 20s. Spent the night, well I couldn't sleep much. But the next morning, bright and early. I was ready.Registration was so intense like I thought the CIA was dishing out the exam hahaha.GAME TIME!!Nothing was going to stop me from leaving a failure. I spent every minute they gave me to take my exam. Not a single second went to waist! I finshed.They handed a trifold paper and said, "Please wait until you exit the building to read your results."Oh man, my heart was fluttering. I knew what I came to do and I couldn't see myself any other way. But there's always that .0001 percent of self doubt. Not alot but just enough. I walked outside into the early afternoon sunshine. A gift of a lovely day. I unfolded it carefully but not slowly. Only to read off my fate:"CONGRATULATIONS. You've successfully passed your California Real Estate Exam".....yadayada. Bowing my head and giving the upmost thanks to the Most High is all I could offer the world in that moment. I did it. I couldn't believe it but what did I expect, I deserved it. All the emotions in life that I had to go through. I also had to use the restroom. Dang.But my Real Estate journey was barely beginning. This has definetly been a life changing experience. This was all foreign to me. It still is today. This whole lifestyle is nothing to how I grew up. The only thing that is from the life I lived is Me, Myself. But my tenacity and ability to learn & adapt to my surroundings always kept me moving forward confidently in life. I am adamant in my pursuit to prosperity and happiness.Thank You for taking time reading my short story.I hope that we may cross paths someday and become apart of each other's journey.This is my own business, I am a Realtor here in Fresno. And if you ever need my guidance in the real estate process. I will be glad to offer you my assistance - David the Realtor

title: REALTOR
description: Do you have an interest in $elling your home?As your listing agent, I can offer my expertise in determining the current value of your home. I will consider the current market conditions in your specific area, along with the uniqness of your home and any upgrades that may be appealing to a buyer. This will give us guidance on determining a sales price to get your home sold in a timely manner. I can point out any red flags, and recommend any repairs or improvements before we hit the market. Addressing some of these issues ahead of time will assist us in obtaining the highest and best offers on your investment.Don't let the internet determine your home's value. Zillow, Realtor.com, and Trulia offer statistical numbers on your home, and don't personally see your property for it's true worth in person. You need an experienced real estate agent like myself to give you a true home market value. If you are curious about what your home is worth in today's market, visitmy home value or give me a call for a "free" home valuation.Ready to purchase your dream home?You may have no idea on where to start in the home buying process, and that's ok. You start by calling me! I will guide you throughout the entire process in becoming a homeowner. Once you have been Preapproved for a home loan, we will search for homes that are available to fit your needs in your price range. Once we find that Gem, the fun begins!There are many items to be address throughout the transaction, and I will walk you through the entire process.  I will negotiate on your behalf to ensure that you are getting the best deal possible on your home purchase. Working with me will give you a fun and exciting, yet pleasant and stress free experience. I look forward to working with you to find the home of your dreams. Oh, and how much will it cost you for my professional representation as your buyer's agent? Nothing! I am compensated by the Seller of your future home. Take a look at what is available today by visitingmy websiteor if you prefer, feel free to downloadmy APP and search away!

title: REALTOR
description: I have been a full-time professional in real estate since 2015, with 15 years of customer service experience. Real estate is not just my job, it's my passion. I like staying educated on the latest industry trends, laws and innovations. Purchasing a home is one of the most important decisions you'll make in your life. A good Real Estate Agent will remove all of the stress from the process and make sure your needs and wants are met every step of the way. This is one thing you can always count on me - Quality service and Integrity by someone you can trust.Hablo Espaol

title: REALTOR
description: Carol MaulHonorary REALTOR for LifeCalifornia Association of REALTORSWhen you are buying or selling property in todays real estate market, it is important to have confidence in your real estate professionals.  My commitment as your Fresno/Clovis Realtor is to provide you with the specialized, personalized real estate service you deserve.I am a realtor in tune with the community. Active financial supporter and participant in numerous community activities, especially in the Arts, I work tirelessly to make our community a better place in which to live.I support of and contribute to the Guarantee Goodwill Network. Since its founding in 2007, this network has contributed over $550,000 to charities in the Greater Fresno area.Owners of multi-family units, I have served on the Advisory Committee of the California Apartment Association, Greater Fresno Division, and chaired its annual awards contest and dinner/ceremony, the Mark of Distinction, for four years.For several years, I secured speakers for the weekly Multiple Listing Service meeting.Carol is a former English teacher and legal assistant, served on the Board of the Junior Company Foundation and served as the President of the Symphony League and on the Board of Directors of the Fresno Philharmonic. She has earned the e-PRO designation upon completing a National Association of REALTORS course in the use of electronic technology.We are members of Hope Lutheran Church in Fresno where we sing in the choir. We also sing in a Community Chorus, Coro Solare.Carol is a graduate of Concordia College in Moorhead, Minnesota, and several times since 1997, she and Ken have coordinated bringing the famed Concordia Choir to Fresno.We are dedicated to keeping our clients informed on trends in the market place, and we assist buyers and sellers in making the best decisions for the most important purchase or sale in a lifetime.If you are considering buying or selling a home in the Fresno or Clovis area or would just like to have additional information about real estate in your area, please call or e-mail us.Thank you for visiting our website!! Please consider it as your on-line source for Fresno and Clovis real estate information and return often for the latest property listing updates.

He always had our best interest in mind and made the process as smooth as possible.Azad provides Strategic Marketing and Transaction Management services to his clients in the Fresno and Clovis markets. S. in Business Marketing and a lover of all things California. title: Sales Manager
description: Real Estate is not just my job, it is my passion.I will help guide you through every step of the process, from helping you get qualified for a home loan to handing you the keys to your new home.It is my mission that you will be so pleased with my efforts that you will recommend me to your friends and family.I find that there are no shortcuts to earning the kind of respect that leads to the referral Im looking for.I know I have to EARN it.I wouldnt want it any other way.During my career I have served as a manager and as a trainer for new realtors getting started in the business.I am well-versed in the real estate industry, and have experience with individual buyer/seller transactions, working with multiple investors on properties, and with flipping homes.My philosophy is simple; share my knowledge and educate my client(s) so that they can make the best possible decisions for their circumstances.I am NOT a salesman looking to up-sell or pressure my clients.I am committed to helping.I find that when I focus on helping my clients achieve their goals  we all win!
